the brain is made of three main parts: the forebrain midbrain and hindbrain the forebrain consists of the cerebrum thalamus and hypothalamus (part of the limbic system) the midbrain consists of the tectum and tegmentum the hindbrain is made of the cerebellum pons and medulla here is a map of brain partsimage : 6 59a4c3ef81a25758f12ed73b 5a79b41ce12f2e2c045cac14 1 screenshot 20180206 at 8 56 30 am#L-RS

blood flows through the veins new information there is a vein called the vena amoris the vena amoris is a vein in the right hand ring finger that is why people don't put there rings on the ring finger on the persons right hand if they do it then the vena amoris will pop and the heart will stop pumping this is a picture of the right hand and all of the veins in it (the blue finger is the ring finger of the right hand you can see the vena amoris vein conected to the finger )image : 6 59a4c3ef81a25758f12ed73b 5a79c476e12f2e2c045cad77 1 venaamorishandweddingringheartlove image : 6 59a4c3ef81a25758f12ed73b 5a79c7ade12f2e2c045caddc 1 heart diagram (en) svg#L-RS
